    • Constructor Detail

      • Schedule

        public Schedule​(java.lang.String csvText)

        Creates a schedule object from a portion of text from a csv file.

        Format:

        NEW LINE;

        MONDAYS TO FRIDAYS;

        TRAIN NO.;[train 1];[train 2];...;

        [Station 1];[arrival time 1];[arrival time 2];...;

        [Station 2];[arrival time 1];[arrival time 2];...;

        ...

        [Station n];[arrival time 1];[arrival time 2];...;

        END;

        SATURDAYS;

        TRAIN NO.; ...

        ...

        END;

        SUNDAYS;

        ...

        END;

        END OF FILE

        Notes: there is no semicolon after the last "END", "SUNDAY" may instead be "SUNDAYS AND PUBLIC HOLIDAYS", a blank arrival time (in fact any string which does not contain ":") means the train doesn't pass the station, any extra text such as blank cells or newline characters between "NEW LINE", [DAY TYPE] "TRAIN NO." are ignored.

        Parameters:
        csvText - the formatted text
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if csvText is incorrectly formatted
